<p>Coach Jess welcomes you!</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <h2 class=\"welcomeIntro\">\n    This is an opinionated catalog of open source JS packages.\n  </h2>\n\n  <p>Libraries come and go. The ecosystem evolves rapidly, and that's a good thing. But it\n  means you can't rely on your bookmarks. Google may not be your best friend either, since\n  it focuses on popular results — established solutions that may not be the best fit for your\n  project.</p>\n\n  <p>This website indexes new packages and is updated roughly once per day, by using both\n  automated scripts and manual curation. It is a complete rewrite and grown-up version of\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/madebyform/react-parts\">React.parts</a>, a tiny project that\n  started a year ago. Even if you are implementing your\n  own solution for your particular problem, this can be a good place to find interesting code\n  to learn from.</p>\n\n  <p>I hope this catalog is as useful to you as it is to me.</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"_1JuVkggfBAzdwG_ERiDuJ1\" data-reactid=\".u58q25s0sg.1.3\"><script src=\"//cdn.carbonads.com/carbon.js?zoneid=1673&amp;serve=C6AILKT&amp;placement=jscoach\" type=\"text/javascript\" async=\"async\" id=\"_carbonads_js\"></script><div id=\"carbonads\"><span><span class=\"carbon-wrap\"><a href=\"//srv.carbonads.net/ads/click/x/GTND4237CVADV27JCAB4YKQWF67DLK3NCY7I5Z3JCEAI627JFTYD627KC6BDLKJYCEADTK3EHJNCLSIZZRLCP7I35MNFV?segment=placement:jscoach;&amp;encredirect=https%3A%2F%2Fad.doubleclick.net%2Fddm%2Ftrackclk%2FN320202.452584BUYSELLADS.COM%2FB10943387.146034821%3Bdc_trk_aid%3D317642025%3Bdc_trk_cid%3D79101461%3Bdc_lat%3D%3Bdc_rdid%3D%3Btag_for_child_directed_treatment%3D\" class=\"carbon-img\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://assets.servedby-buysellads.com/p/manage/asset/id/36878\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"100\" width=\"130\" style=\"max-width: 130px;\"></a><a href=\"//srv.carbonads.net/ads/click/x/GTND4237CVADV27JCAB4YKQWF67DLK3NCY7I5Z3JCEAI627JFTYD627KC6BDLKJYCEADTK3EHJNCLSIZZRLCP7I35MNFV?segment=placement:jscoach;&amp;encredirect=https%3A%2F%2Fad.doubleclick.net%2Fddm%2Ftrackclk%2FN320202.452584BUYSELLADS.COM%2FB10943387.146034821%3Bdc_trk_aid%3D317642025%3Bdc_trk_cid%3D79101461%3Bdc_lat%3D%3Bdc_rdid%3D%3Btag_for_child_directed_treatment%3D\" class=\"carbon-text\" target=\"_blank\">What will your code do? class=\\\"welcomeIntro\\\"\\u003e\\n    This is an opinionated catalog of open source JS packages.\\n  \\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\n  \\u003cp\\u003eLibraries come and go. The ecosystem evolves rapidly, and that's a good thing. But it\\n  means you can't rely on your bookmarks. Google may not be your best friend either, since\\n  it focuses on popular results — established solutions that may not be the best fit for your\\n  project.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\n  \\u003cp\\u003eThis website indexes new packages and is updated roughly once per day, by using both\\n  automated scripts and manual curation. Here's why:\\n  \\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\n  \\u003cul class=\\\"more\\\"\\u003e\\n    \\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eAdd collections.\\u003c/strong\\u003e More collections will be added in the future.\\n      You'll be able to customize them and pin the ones that matter to you most.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n    \\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003ePin packages.\\u003c/strong\\u003e You could use your pinned packages as bookmarks or\\n      simply as a temporary stash area for your work in hand.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n    \\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eCreate projects.\\u003c/strong\\u003e You'll be able to upload a \\u003ccode\\u003epackage.json\\u003c/code\\u003e\\n      file to filter out dependencies that are not met.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n    \\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eImprove the catalog.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Logged in users can help fix packages mislabeled\\n      with the wrong collections.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n  \\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\n  \\u003cp class=\\\"more\\\"\\u003e\\n    Some of these features are still being implemented, and therefore registrations are\\n    still closed.
